  "title": "Kitchen Crew & Cashier",
  "description": "<p>To apply or find out more, please contact</p><p><strong> Leong Jia Wei</strong></p><p>(Reg No: R25157456) on </p><p>WhatsApp</p><p><strong>+65 80358497</strong></p><p> or</p><p>email</p><p><a href=\"mailto:jiawei@placement.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">jiawei@placement.com.sg<br /><br /><br /><br /></a># Overview #</p><p>My client is a Spicy Tofu Hot Plate brand in the Central/Town Area\nlooking for a Cashier and Kitchen Crew.</p><p># Key Responsibilities #</p><p>•     Prepare dishes according to instructions and standardized\nrecopies </p><p>•     Operate the POS system, handle cash, and manage digital\npayments.</p><p>•     Maintain stall cleanliness, including wiping counters,\nwashing equipment, clearing trash, and keeping the workspace organised.</p><p>•     Restock ingredients</p><p>•     Follow food safety and hygiene guidelines (SFA requirements,\nhandwashing, glove use, proper storage).</p><p>•     Manage customer orders quickly and accurately, especially\nduring peak periods.</p><p>•     Assist with opening and closing duties — prepping\ningredients, turning on/off machines, counting stock, and closing reports.</p><p>•     Other forms of basic customer service, including addressing\ncomplaints or special requests.</p><p># Requirements #</p><p>•     Speaks English and Mandarin Chinese for internal\ncommunication and customer interactions</p><p>•     Work Hours: 1000-2200</p><p>•     Able to stand for long hours and handle fast-paced\nenvironments.</p><p>•     Salary scales up based on skills and experience</p><p>#Benefits#</p><p>•     1 staff meal provided per day</p><p>•     Rest enabled during non-busy periods when no customers</p>",
